    "reviewedByUser": false,
    "content": "# Specification: Isolate Agent Chat from Board Project Changes\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\n\nWhen a user changes the project in the board view, the entire Kanban view including the agent chat panel is being force-refreshed. This causes disruption to any ongoing agent conversations and creates a jarring user experience. The agent chat should remain independent and unaffected by board-level project changes.\n\n## 2. User Story\n\nAs a **developer using Automaker**, I want **the agent chat to remain stable when I switch projects in the board view**, so that **I can continue my agent conversations without interruption while exploring different projects on the board**.\n\n## 3. Acceptance Criteria\n\n**Happy Path:**\n- GIVEN I have an active agent chat session open\n- WHEN I change the project in the board view\n- THEN the agent chat remains visible with the same conversation and is not refreshed\n\n**Edge Case - New Session:**\n- GIVEN I have no active agent chat session\n- WHEN I change the project in the board view\n- THEN the agent chat panel remains in its empty state without unnecessary re-renders\n\n**Edge Case - Different Project Agent:**\n- GIVEN I have an agent chat for Project A open\n- WHEN I switch the board to Project B\n- THEN the agent chat for Project A continues uninterrupted (user can choose to switch agent sessions separately)\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- GIVEN the board view encounters an error during project switch\n- WHEN the board refreshes due to error recovery\n- THEN the agent chat state is preserved independently\n\n## 4. Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Affected Files | `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx`, `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/agent-chat-panel.tsx`, `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-board-project.ts` (if exists), `apps/ui/src/store/app-store.ts` |\n| Dependencies | React, Zustand |\n| Constraints | Must maintain state isolation between board and agent components |\n| Patterns to Follow | Zustand store patterns, React key management, component memoization |\n\n## 5. Non-Goals\n\n- This feature does NOT change how the agent chat itself works\n- This feature does NOT modify the agent session management logic\n- This feature does NOT change the project switching API\n- This feature does NOT affect the files view refresh behavior (files view SHOULD still refresh)\n\n## 6. Implementation Tasks\n\n```tasks\n## Phase 1: Investigation & Analysis\n- [ ] T001: Analyze board-view.tsx to understand current project switching mechanism | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx\n- [ ] T002: Analyze agent-chat-panel.tsx to understand its dependencies on board state | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/agent-chat-panel.tsx\n- [ ] T003: Review app-store.ts for project state management | File: apps/ui/src/store/app-store.ts\n\n## Phase 2: Core Implementation\n- [ ] T004: Isolate agent chat state from board project changes | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx\n- [ ] T005: Memoize agent-chat-panel to prevent unnecessary re-renders | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/agent-chat-panel.tsx\n- [ ] T006: Ensure board and files view still refresh correctly on project change | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx\n\n## Phase 3: Verification\n- [ ] T007: Test that agent chat persists through project switches | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx\n```\n\n## 7. Success Metrics\n\n- Agent chat component does not unmount/remount when board project changes\n- Agent chat conversation history is preserved during project switch\n- Board view and files view still update correctly when project changes\n- No React key warnings or unnecessary re-renders in console\n\n## 8. Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Agent chat may have hidden dependencies on board project state | Thorough analysis of component props and hooks before changes |\n| Over-memoization could cause stale state issues | Use appropriate dependency arrays and test state updates |\n| Files view might accidentally be isolated too | Explicitly verify files view still refreshes |\n\n---",
    "generatedAt": "2026-02-09T16:19:51.284Z",
